.TH "efi_low_alloc_above" 9 "efi_low_alloc_above" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
efi_low_alloc_above \- allocate pages at or above given address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "efi_status_t" efi_low_alloc_above
.BI "(unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "unsigned long align "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long min "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
size of the memory area to allocate
.IP "align" 12
minimum alignment of the allocated memory area. It should
a power of two.
.IP "addr" 12
on exit the address of the allocated memory
.IP "min" 12
minimum address to used for the memory allocation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate at the lowest possible address that is not below \fImin\fP as
EFI_LOADER_DATA. The allocated pages are aligned according to \fIalign\fP but at
least EFI_ALLOC_ALIGN. The first allocated page will not below the address
given by \fImin\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
status code
